Bauchi State police command has arrested a 30-year-old man, Yahuza Musa of Unguwar Sarki Hausawa in Miya Village of Ganjuwa for allegedly committing sodomy. DAILY POST reports that the Police Public Relations Officer of the command, SP Ahmed Wakili disclosed this in a press statement made available to journalists in Bauchi. He said that the suspect allegedly lured his victim, 12 years old of the same address and had anal sexual intercourse with him. The PPRO said that “on the 20/3/2022 at about 0900hrs, one Abdullahi Kano of Unguwar Sarki Hausawa in Miya village of Ganjuwa LGA, reported at the Ganjuwa Police Divisional Headquarters that on the 19/3/2022 at about 2130hrs, one 30-year-old Yahaya Musa of the same address lured one 12-year-old Abdulkadir into his barbing shop deceitfully and forcefully had anal sexual intercourse with the victim twice.” He said that during interrogation, the suspect voluntarily confessed to the crime, adding that investigation was ongoing, after which the suspect will be charged to court. Also, “on the 18/03/2022 at about 1440hrs, one Abdullahi Ahmadu, 70yrs, of Ligada Jula village, Giade LGA, Bauchi State reported that on the 16/03/2022 at about 1700hrs, one Musa Saleh, 20yrs, of same address lured one Hajiya (not real name) and had unlawful carnal knowledge of her without her consent. Wakil said that during interrogation, the suspect voluntarily confessed to the commission of crime, adding that investigation was ongoing, after which the suspect will be charged to court. The police spokesman also disclosed that on 20/03/2022, at about 1300hrs, one Liatu M. Gaius of Bayara Bauchi State, reported at E’ Division Yelwa that on 19/03/2022 at about 2300hrs,one Jonathan Manasseh, aged 20yrs, of Yelwan Kagadama Bauchi State, abducted her 17-year-old daughter Christiana (not real name) to his room at Yelwan Kagadama and had carnal knowledge of her without her consent. He said that during interrogation, the suspect confessed to the crime, adding that investigation is ongoing, after which the suspect will be charged to court.